        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(cost): estimate usage cost when API returns cost.total=0 but pricing is known",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nDeepSeek V4 API returns `usage.cost.total: 0` in completion responses. OpenClaw has known positive pricing configured, but the cost scan logic accepts the $0 as fact — Control UI \"Spend\" shows ¥0.00 for all DeepSeek V4 usage.\n\n**Root cause**: `scanTranscriptFile` only estimates when `costTotal === undefined`. When API returns `cost.total: 0` and `isModelPricingKnown(cost)` is true, the $0 is kept as-is.\n\n**Fix**: Extend estimate condition to `costTotal === undefined || costTotal === 0`, plus bump `USAGE_COST_CACHE_VERSION` 4→5 so existing users' cached $0 data gets rebuilt.\n\nCloses #97047\n\n## Change Type\n\n- [x] Bug fix\n\n## Scope\n\n- [x] Infrastructure (cost/usage aggregation)\n\n## Evidence\n\n**Code change** (`src/infra/session-cost-usage.ts:1168`):\n```diff\n- } else if (entry.costTotal === undefined) {\n+ } else if (entry.costTotal === undefined || entry.costTotal === 0) {\n```\n\n**Cache invalidation** (`src/infra/session-cost-usage.ts:81`):\n```diff\n- const USAGE_COST_CACHE_VERSION = 4;\n+ const USAGE_COST_CACHE_VERSION = 5;\n```\n\n**Pricing**: DeepSeek V4 Flash: input ¥0.14/10K, output ¥0.28/10K. V4 Pro: input ¥1.74/10K, output ¥3.48/10K.\n\n**Before fix**: `cost.total: 0` from API → `entry.costTotal = 0` → `isModelPricingKnown(cost) = true` → skips both unknown-pricing branch and estimate branch → **$0 kept as fact**.\n\n**After fix**: `cost.total: 0` → `entry.costTotal === 0` matches new condition → `estimateUsageCost({ usage, cost })` called → **cost estimated from token counts × known pricing**. Example: 95029 input + 465 output → estimated ~¥1.33.\n\n**Regression test**: Added `\"estimates cost when pricing is known but API returns cost.total=0 (DeepSeek V4)\"` — creates transcript with DeepSeek V4 tokens + $0 API cost + known pricing, verifies `totalCost > 0` and `missingCostEntries = 0`.\n\n## Security Impact\n\n- New permissions? No\n- Secrets handling changed? No\n- New network calls? No\n",
